idget configuration contains a lot of useful options:\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/weather_screen_admin.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1861\" alt=\"weather_screen_admin\" src=\"{$page_url}/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/weather_screen_admin.png\" width=\"361\" height=\"576\" /></a>\r\n\r\nBelow we have described all available options:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>City name</strong> – name displayed in the widget</li>\r\n	<li><strong>WOEID</strong> – where on earth identifier – it is an ID used to identify the specific place – you can find WOEID for your city on the linked in the widget options page.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Time Offset</strong> – useful if the time on your server is different than time on your timezone.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Show City Name</strong> –  you can enable/disable showing the city name</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Show humidity</strong> – you can enable/disable showing the humidity</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Show wind</strong> – you can enable/disable showing the wind</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Temperature unit</strong> – temperate unit used in the forecast – Celsius or Fahrenheit</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Show current conditions</strong> – you can enable/disable display of the current conditions. It is especially useful when the current conditions are not available for your city.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Show forecast</strong> – you can enable/disable display of the forecast for the upcoming two days.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Iconset</strong> – you can select the iconset used in the widget. For the dark style please use the light icons, for other styles please use the dark iconset.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Icon size (current weather)</strong> – icon size in the current weather conditions</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Icon size (forecast)</strong> – icon size in the forecast.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','GK Weather','','publish','open','open','','gk-weather','','','2014-03-21 12:34:09','2014-03-21 12:34:09','',756,'{$page_url}/?page_id=1859',